# Liqid Workspace Agent Instructions  ## 1. Workspace Overview  The Liqid workspace is a monorepo structured to support the Liqid design system ecosystem. It is composed of independent yet interconnected packages managed as Git submodules.  ### Monorepo Structure  *   **Root**: `/Users/user/Documents/VSCodeProjects/liqid` *   **Packages (Submodules)**:     *   **liqid-components** (`./liqid-components`): Core React component library implementing the Liqid Glass design system. Focuses on atomic elements (Buttons, Inputs, Cards).     *   **liqid-ui** (`./liqid-ui`): Desktop UI library providing high-level window management, shells, and desktop environment components.     *   **liqid-docs** (`./liqid-docs`): Documentation website and component playground. (Package name: `liqid-playground`).     *   **portfolio** (`./portfolio`): A full-featured desktop environment demo application showcasing the Liqid ecosystem. Includes a backend server.  ---  ## 2. Package Details & Analysis  ### A. liqid-components (Core Library) *   **Path**: `./liqid-components` *   **Type**: Library (Rslib) -> ESM + CJS *   **Purpose**: Foundational UI elements with "Liqid Glass" styling. *   **Tech Stack**: React 19, Tailwind v4, Biome. *   **Dependencies**: `swr`, `wouter`. *   **Key Commands**:     *   `npm run build`: Build library.     *   `npm run dev`: Watch mode.     *   `npm run lint`: Biome check.  ### B. liqid-ui (Desktop Environment) *   **Path**: `./liqid-ui` *   **Type**: Library (Rslib) -> ESM + CJS *   **Purpose**: OS-like experience components (WindowManager, Desktop, Taskbar). *   **Tech Stack**: React 19, Tailwind v4, Biome. *   **Dependencies**: `@tabler/icons-react`, `liqid` (local file dependency). *   **Key Files**:     *   `src/components/`: Windowing components.     *   `src/hooks/`: Logic for window management.  ### C. portfolio (Demo Application) *   **Path**: `./portfolio` *   **Type**: Application (Rsbuild) *   **Purpose**: A "Web OS" portfolio site. *   **Tech Stack**:      *   **Frontend**: React 19, Tailwind v4, Rsbuild.     *   **Backend**: Node.js, Express, Better-SQLite3, Kysely, Nodemailer. *   **Structure**:     *   `src/components/`: UI components.     *   `src/server/`: Backend API.     *   `src/components/Apps/`: Windowed applications. *   **Development**:     *   `npm run dev`: Starts Frontend + Backend concurrently.     *   `npm run dev:phonebooth`: Dev for specific phonebooth submodule app.  ### D. liqid-docs (Playground) *   **Path**: `./liqid-docs` *   **Type**: Application (Rsbuild) *   **Purpose**: Documentation and component playground. *   **Package Name**: `liqid-playground`. *   **Tech Stack**: React 19, Tailwind v4, Rsbuild.  ---  ## 3. Development Guidelines & Standards  ### Workflow 1.  **Check Requirements**:     *   **TODO.md**: Check `.agent/TODO.md` (root) or project-specific TODOs.     *   **COMPONENTS.md**: If working on components, check/update progress in `liqid-components/COMPONENTS.md` or `liqid-ui/COMPONENTS.md`. 2.  **Implementation**:     *   Create 1 function per component file.     *   Use **Tailwind v4** for styling.     *   Ensure "Liqid Glass" aesthetics (blur, transparency, gradients). 3.  **Verification**:     *   **Lint**: `npm run lint` (Biome) is MANDATORY before completion.     *   **Build**: `npm run build` to verify no breaking changes.     *   **Cross-Link**: If working in `portfolio`, ensure changes in `liqid-ui` or `liqid-components` are reflected (link/install may be needed).  ### Status Icons (for documentation) | Icon | Title   | Use         | | ---- | ------- | ----------- | | â¬œ   | Todo    | Not started | | ðŸ”„   | Active  | In progress | | âœ…   | Done    | Completed   | | ðŸš«   | Blocked | Needs input |  ---  ## 4. Agent Operational Rules  ### Monorepo Awareness *   **Context**: Always be aware of which submodule you are in. Do not introduce circular dependencies. *   **Refactoring**: If you build a reusable component in `portfolio`, suggest moving it to `liqid-com